     1   5226            22/12/2005 13:04:03 luebbe                         <!DOCTYPE sect1 SYSTEM "../../../dtd/dblite.dtd">
     2   3982            24/07/2005 13:06:25 steveking                      <sect1 id="tsvn-DUG-relocate">
     3   3982            24/07/2005 13:06:25 steveking                      	<title>Relocating a working copy</title>
     4   3982            24/07/2005 13:06:25 steveking                      	<indexterm>
     5   3982            24/07/2005 13:06:25 steveking                      		<primary>relocate</primary>
     6   3982            24/07/2005 13:06:25 steveking                      	</indexterm>
     7   3982            24/07/2005 13:06:25 steveking                      	<?dbhh topicname="HIDD_RELOCATE"?>
     8   3982            24/07/2005 13:06:25 steveking                      	<para>
     9   3982            24/07/2005 13:06:25 steveking                      		<figure id="tsvn-DUG-relocate-dia-1">
    10   3982            24/07/2005 13:06:25 steveking                      			<title>The Relocate Dialog</title>
    11   4977            19/11/2005 15:49:17 steveking                      			<graphic fileref="../images/Relocate.png"/>
    12   3982            24/07/2005 13:06:25 steveking                      		</figure>
    13   3982            24/07/2005 13:06:25 steveking                      		If your repository has for some reason changed it's
    14   3982            24/07/2005 13:06:25 steveking                      		location (IP/URL). Maybe you're even stuck and can't
    15   3982            24/07/2005 13:06:25 steveking                      		commit and you don't want to checkout your working
    16   3982            24/07/2005 13:06:25 steveking                      		copy again from the new location and to move all your
    17   3982            24/07/2005 13:06:25 steveking                      		changed data back into the new working copy,
    18   3982            24/07/2005 13:06:25 steveking                      		<menuchoice>
    19   3982            24/07/2005 13:06:25 steveking                      			<guimenu>TortoiseSVN</guimenu>
    20   3982            24/07/2005 13:06:25 steveking                      			<guimenuitem>Relocate</guimenuitem>
    21   3982            24/07/2005 13:06:25 steveking                      		</menuchoice>
    22   3982            24/07/2005 13:06:25 steveking                      		is the command you are looking for. It basically
    23   3982            24/07/2005 13:06:25 steveking                      		does very little: it scans all "entries" files in the
    24   3982            24/07/2005 13:06:25 steveking                      		<filename>.svn</filename> folder and changes the URL of
    25   3982            24/07/2005 13:06:25 steveking                      		the entries to the new value.
    26   3982            24/07/2005 13:06:25 steveking                      	</para>
    27   3982            24/07/2005 13:06:25 steveking                      	<warning>
    28   3982            24/07/2005 13:06:25 steveking                      		<para>
    29   4924            11/11/2005 23:16:25 simonlarge                     			<emphasis>This is a very infrequently used operation</emphasis>.
    30   4929            13/11/2005 09:18:18 luebbe                         			The relocate command is <emphasis>only</emphasis> used if the URL of the
    31   4929            13/11/2005 09:18:18 luebbe                         			repository root has changed. Possible reasons are:
    32   4929            13/11/2005 09:18:18 luebbe                         			<itemizedlist>
    33   4929            13/11/2005 09:18:18 luebbe                         				<listitem>
    34   4929            13/11/2005 09:18:18 luebbe                         					<para>The IP address of the server has changed.</para>
    35   4929            13/11/2005 09:18:18 luebbe                         				</listitem>
    36   4929            13/11/2005 09:18:18 luebbe                         				<listitem>
    37   4929            13/11/2005 09:18:18 luebbe                         					<para>The protocol has changed (e.g. http:// to https://).</para>
    38   4929            13/11/2005 09:18:18 luebbe                         				</listitem>
    39   4929            13/11/2005 09:18:18 luebbe                         				<listitem>
    40   4929            13/11/2005 09:18:18 luebbe                         					<para>The repository root path in the server setup has changed.</para>
    41   4929            13/11/2005 09:18:18 luebbe                         				</listitem>
    42   4929            13/11/2005 09:18:18 luebbe                         			</itemizedlist>
    43   4929            13/11/2005 09:18:18 luebbe                         			Put another way, you need to relocate when your working copy is referring
    44   4929            13/11/2005 09:18:18 luebbe                         			to the same location in the same repository, but the repository itself
    45   4924            11/11/2005 23:16:25 simonlarge                     			has moved.
    46   3982            24/07/2005 13:06:25 steveking                      		</para>
    47   3982            24/07/2005 13:06:25 steveking                      		<para>
    48   4929            13/11/2005 09:18:18 luebbe                         			It does not apply if:
    49   4929            13/11/2005 09:18:18 luebbe                         			<itemizedlist>
    50   4929            13/11/2005 09:18:18 luebbe                         				<listitem>
    51   4929            13/11/2005 09:18:18 luebbe                         					<para>
    52   4929            13/11/2005 09:18:18 luebbe                         						You want to move to a different Subversion repository. In that case
    53   4929            13/11/2005 09:18:18 luebbe                         						you should perform a clean checkout from the new repository location.
    54   4929            13/11/2005 09:18:18 luebbe                         					</para>
    55   4929            13/11/2005 09:18:18 luebbe                         				</listitem>
    56   4929            13/11/2005 09:18:18 luebbe                         				<listitem>
    57   4929            13/11/2005 09:18:18 luebbe                         					<para>
    58   4929            13/11/2005 09:18:18 luebbe                         						You want to switch to a different branch or directory within the 
    59   4929            13/11/2005 09:18:18 luebbe                         						same repository. To do that you should use
    60   4929            13/11/2005 09:18:18 luebbe                         						<menuchoice>
    61   4929            13/11/2005 09:18:18 luebbe                         							<guimenu>TortoiseSVN</guimenu>
    62   4929            13/11/2005 09:18:18 luebbe                         							<guimenuitem>Switch...</guimenuitem>
    63   4929            13/11/2005 09:18:18 luebbe                         						</menuchoice>.
    64   4929            13/11/2005 09:18:18 luebbe                         						Read <xref linkend="tsvn-DUG-switch-1"/> for more information.
    65   4929            13/11/2005 09:18:18 luebbe                         					</para>
    66   4929            13/11/2005 09:18:18 luebbe                         				</listitem>
    67   4929            13/11/2005 09:18:18 luebbe                         			</itemizedlist>
    68   3982            24/07/2005 13:06:25 steveking                      		</para>
    69   4924            11/11/2005 23:16:25 simonlarge                     		<para>
    70   4929            13/11/2005 09:18:18 luebbe                         			If you use relocate in either of the cases above, it
    71   4929            13/11/2005 09:18:18 luebbe                         			<emphasis>will corrupt your working copy</emphasis> and you will get many
    72   4924            11/11/2005 23:16:25 simonlarge                     			unexplainable error messages while updating, committing, etc.
    73   4924            11/11/2005 23:16:25 simonlarge                     			Once that has happened, the only fix is a fresh checkout.
    74   4924            11/11/2005 23:16:25 simonlarge                     		</para>
    75   3982            24/07/2005 13:06:25 steveking                      	</warning>
    76   3982            24/07/2005 13:06:25 steveking                      </sect1>
